Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.31,0:00:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hateful feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.90,0:00:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurtful feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.06,0:00:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unforgivable feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.98,0:00:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To face ones own feelings is akin to\Nthrowing oneself into a bottomless pit,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.58,0:00:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or setting sail on an endless sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not look there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.79,0:00:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though you search your soul on the dark,\Nheaving waves, you must never look in that place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.45,0:01:04.79,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The blue moon illuminated
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.83,0:01:08.75,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}your wandering shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.38,0:01:13.26,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I could never tell you all I wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.26,0:01:18.18,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,250)}It was so very frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.26,0:01:22.06,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I think about your faked smile,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.64,0:01:26.69,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}and forget all the hot tears we shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.14,0:01:29.36,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}What do these empty husks,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.40,0:01:35.19,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}those empty eyes of yours, reflect, my dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.95,0:01:40.41,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The transient quarter moon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.78,0:01:42.58,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,100)}hides in a rift in the clouds,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.54,0:01:44.95,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(100,300)}as darkness seeps up from the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.00,0:01:49.42,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Tell me the truth, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.75,0:01:51.59,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Are you so despondent
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.67,0:01:55.97,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,0)}that you still sit alone, sighing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.47,0:01:57.97,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}Finale
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.36,0:02:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are you saying that your sister\Nwas sealed in here, fifty years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.53,0:02:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and still wanders aimlessly across the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dragon’s Triangle itself is a Mononoke, born\Nfrom the malice contained within this Utsurobune.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.42,0:02:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn’t that the Mononoke’s Truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.79,0:02:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we should open the Utsurobune,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and give her a proper funeral,\Nthus allowing our ship to escape this wretched sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.35,0:02:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y—You want to open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.56,0:02:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s simply too frightening to contemplate!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.27,0:02:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she’s been trapped in there for fifty years!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.98,0:02:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must want to get out. I would.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.36,0:02:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m afraid! Afraid!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No-one could stay alive in there for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.37,0:03:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she’s been dead for fifty years,\Nthen her body would have rotted away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the more reason for us to save\NGenkei-dono’s unfortunate sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.59,0:03:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, this is the monk’s most noble calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.38,0:03:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I convince you not to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.47,0:03:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we really open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.22,0:03:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do not wish to roam this\Nsea forever as a Mononoke, then yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.19,0:03:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I want to become a Mononoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.19,0:03:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, didn’t you come here in order to\Nput those who’ve become Mononoke to rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.46,0:03:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave, ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.59,0:04:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is harder than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop watching and come help us, Mr. Medicine Seller!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, once more!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave, ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.23,0:04:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave, ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.73,0:04:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don’t you ever say when you’re going to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.32,0:05:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyou and I were born on a small island not far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our parents died at sea while we were still young.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She and I lived together, and there were no other\Nchildren our age around, so we were always together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got along so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.56,0:05:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, perhaps we got along {\i1}too{\i0} well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was fifteen, I entered the monastery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.57,0:05:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the tradition on that island,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.86,0:05:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Oyou and I were compelled to follow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:02.84,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,His sister…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:03.34,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(640,619,640,690,200,0)\t(50,200,\c&HE9ECF1&\3c&H262B32&)}His sister…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.34,0:06:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She’s completely gone. Neither…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.30,0:06:05.05,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.59,0:06:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,hide nor hair of her to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.47,0:06:08.01,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyou!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From then on, I took on the name of Genkei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I left the island, and undertook the\Nmost intense form of purification training.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.11,0:06:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Many could not stand the training, and dropped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bore through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than once, I wanted to forget about Oyou entirely,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.12,0:06:34.99,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she thought about me every single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:42.46,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So{\i0} many goldfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She prayed constantly for me to become a good monk.{}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.63,0:06:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew, though, that as brother and sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.26,0:06:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we could never be joined together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was certain that Oyou was in he—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.56,0:07:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that your sister did not become
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a Mononoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what exactly {\i1}is{\i0} the Truth behind this Mononoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.95,0:07:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is measuring our distance from the Mononoke again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is not merely measuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have sent it to show us
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.76,0:07:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Mononoke’s Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.55,0:07:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you tell me, now,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.43,0:07:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what the connection is between your sister\Nand this Utsurobune from fifty years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.98,0:07:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The scale is going to bring the Truth{\alpha&HFF&} to light?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.07,0:07:51.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The scale is going to bring the Truth to light?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:08:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Buddhist path strays far from the path of flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How I dreamed of being together with Oyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.96,0:08:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I chose to continue my training.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.30,0:08:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know not whether it was to purify myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.18,0:08:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or merely to escape the source of my impure thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely that was the true reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.65,0:08:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be with Oyou, though we could never be married.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.99,0:08:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.08,0:08:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.75,0:08:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even Oyou would one day be married.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.21,0:08:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did not want to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.43,0:09:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I thought of it, I felt my mind\Nturn to terrible, unbearable thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.52,0:09:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.15,0:09:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama, had I but known\Nyour soul had become so impure!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.15,0:09:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It did not become that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My soul was always impure, Sougen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am so sorry you had to have a teacher like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But,{} why did Oyou-san board the Utsurobune?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.01,0:09:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.72,0:09:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you see…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.23,0:09:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five years after I had started my training,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.69,0:09:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Dragon’s Triangle had gained notoriety,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.53,0:09:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even before the Ayakashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.99,0:10:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for it had claimed many, many ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.37,0:10:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That very autumn, more than\Nhalf of the island’s ships were sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.63,0:10:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard of this in writings from my home, and\Nbecame convinced it was tied to my own fortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.51,0:10:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They did not write explicitly that they\Nwould conduct a sacrifice to appease the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I could tell that many wished for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought to sacrifice myself, rather than\Ncontinue running in fear of my very nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people of the island wished for it,\Nand it would certainly have been easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The islanders heard of my decision, and built an Utsurobune.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.55,0:10:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Utsurobune…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.59,0:10:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that was where the Utsurobune was launched.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.59,0:11:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, though, should you not\Nbe inside the Utsurobune, Genkei-dono?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.97,0:11:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did it come to be that Oyou-san replaced you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The islanders built a beautiful ship indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.49,0:11:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This very same Utsurobune.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it was first built, it was a work of art indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the morning I was to board\Nthe ship, I was reunited with Oyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.59,0:11:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was a gorgeous young woman of sixteen years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.76,0:11:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I should never have seen her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, though, I could not\Nboard the Utsurobune after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.69,0:11:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I became so afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.32,0:12:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that I could never ride the Utsurobune,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and so gain enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.04,0:12:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyou mistook my fear and cowardice for kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.30,0:12:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew better than anyone that I was unworthy of her pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.39,0:12:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time of the ship’s departure was imminent, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The islanders demanded that I be sacrificed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.57,0:12:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Oyou said,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“I will board the Utsurobune in your place, my brother.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.37,0:12:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I told her I could not allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.08,0:12:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After preparations were complete for\Nthe ship’s launch, Oyou spoke to me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.05,0:13:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I cannot be married to you,\NBrother, then I will go unmarried to my death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While you were away training, I\Ndreamt of you every day, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it means the end to this unbearable\Npain, I will gladly set forth in the Utsurobune.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.20,0:13:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could not believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.28,0:13:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyou and I were thinking the same thing, all that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.46,0:13:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After she told me, we should have\Nentered the Utsurobune together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.55,0:13:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was simply too afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran from my homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.31,0:13:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my mind, I reached out for Oyou and\Ntold her that we would be together soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.81,0:14:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did not even have the courage to take my own life, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran all the way to the monastery at\NMount Fuji, where I completed my training.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My training was renowned as the strictest in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.21,0:14:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but for fifty years, I continued to think about Oyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.97,0:14:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, Oyou-san rode the Utsurobune,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.01,0:14:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and became a Mononoke after fifty years of travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.64,0:14:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor Oyou-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.52,0:14:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong? What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.03,0:14:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was not Oyou-san’s malice that\Nbrought forth the Mononoke on this sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.20,0:14:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.21,0:14:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.92,0:15:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-dono,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.34,0:15:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that eye that you are hiding…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.38,0:15:05.88,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.26,0:15:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.55,0:15:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has been watching all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.60,0:15:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You feared Oyou-san. You feared your own heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.06,0:15:22.27,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama’s eye is right…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear gave rise to fear, and soon they became a\Nshadow, dark beyond human understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.99,0:15:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It separated from you, and wandered the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:35.45,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.83,0:15:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}you!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.58,0:15:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—Is that what I have been afraid of for the past fifty years?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.92,0:15:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Oyou… Where is Oyou?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.22,0:15:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She did not become a Mononoke,\Nbut rather became one with the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:16:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after willingly sacrificing herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.64,0:16:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Umi Bozu is a part of you that\Nyou’ve kept hidden and contained all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Separate!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.79,0:16:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you, Genkei-dono…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To kill this Mononoke would mean killing your very soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.96,0:16:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would mean the return of your real feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.59,0:16:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,those which caused your soul to split in\Ntwo, those which you have always denied.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask you, do you still wish this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.27,0:16:45.85,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Brother, I’m so glad to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve been promoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:51.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should really keep advancing,\Nand live a prosperous life as a monk,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:52.69,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I will happily board the Utsurobune in your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.11,0:16:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not throw it all away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.20,0:16:54.57,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I’m so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m saved! Is she an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.41,0:17:00.20,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Before I take your place, I wish only one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.20,0:17:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Money?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.54,0:17:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t have any.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:06.88,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I have always wanted to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I cannot be married to you,\NBrother, then I will go unmarried to my death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.23,0:17:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel so relieved, oddly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.07,0:17:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister confessed her love to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.79,0:17:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did not really ever love my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.67,0:17:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was such a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:18:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the joy of being loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.52,0:18:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It took me a long time indeed to feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.70,0:18:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.20,0:18:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.71,0:18:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Release!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.42,0:18:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Release.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.90,0:19:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am free!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’ll be fine. He’s breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.87,0:19:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was actually quite handsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He looks like he’s smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.85,0:20:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyou?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.78,0:20:30.29,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Without you, I just can’t smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:41.34,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I walk this banal town,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.34,0:20:47.43,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}feeling such intense emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.97,0:20:53.81,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I know that if I could treasure them and live on,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:21:03.11,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I would need nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:11.29,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}The summer flowers that bloomed in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.29,0:21:17.58,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Come falling down, dancing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.67,0:21:20.92,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I can barely recall the night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.92,0:21:24.22,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}where they all came tumbling down,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:35.06,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}so what I can still recall is all the more precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.32,0:21:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.69,0:22:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will never{\alpha&HFF&} forget you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.27,0:22:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will never forget you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.03,0:22:29.99,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}The End
